## Google Sheets Access (Updated 2026-03-18)

### The Problem
`gog sheets get` caches responses **per range**. If you query `A1:N5`, it caches that range. Future queries to the same range return cached (stale) data even if the sheet has been updated.

### Verified Working
- `gog sheets metadata` — Always fresh ✅
- `gog sheets update` — Works fine ✅
- Service account via Python script — Always fresh ✅

### The Fix
**For all data reads, use the service account script instead of `gog sheets get`:**
```bash
source venv/bin/activate
python3 sheet_reader.py <spreadsheet_id> "<range>"
```
Example:
```bash
source venv/bin/activate
python3 sheet_reader.py 1nL36orjiVc02ianymDLZMlNbvF_kP6LyFVEZmbranco "Extraction Manifest!A1:N50"
```

**Service account file:** `/Users/m/Library/Application Support/gogcli/sa-bW9uZXktcGVubnlAbW9uZXlwZW5ueS00ODkwMTQuaWFtLmdzZXJ2aWNlYWNjb3VudC5jb20.json`

**Script location:** `/Users/m/.openclaw/workspace-q/sheet_reader.py`

**Virtual environment:** `/Users/m/.openclaw/workspace-q/venv/` (already has google-api-python-client installed)

